In backend/main.mo, in the function buildShuffledSectionFromArray, replace the entire existing `let groupExercises = exercises.filter(...)` block (currently using invalid Motoko dot-syntax like `e.primaryMuscleGroup.toLower()` / `group.toLower()`) with the following exact Motoko code, using the already-imported Text module:

```motoko
    let groupExercises = exercises.filter(func(e) {
      Text.equal(
        Text.toLowercase(e.primaryMuscleGroup),
        Text.toLowercase(group)
      )
    });
```

Keep all other logic exactly as-is, including any `Debug.print` statements and `TEST_RECOVERY_MODE = true`.
